Three people have died and several others severely injured
following a tragic road accident on the Mombasa - Nairobi highway. The road carnage that occurred on Saturday in Tumbuni area near
Sultan Hamud in Makueni County involved a 46-seater matatu and a truck. According to police reports, the matatu collided head-on with the
oncoming truck on the busy highway. Makueni Police Commander Joseph Ole Napeiyan confirmed the
accident saying he will issue comprehensive details later.